import googlemaps
from gtts import gTTS
import IPython.display as display
from geopy.geocoders import Nominatim

# ✅ Set Up Google Maps API Key
GMAPS_API_KEY = "AIzaSyCkPbdQOHSBgf60hxRpYBz3kAO31L9Z7Ac"  # Replace with your API key
gmaps = googlemaps.Client(key=GMAPS_API_KEY)

# ✅ Function to Get Coordinates from Address
def get_coordinates(location):
    geolocator = Nominatim(user_agent="nishwanthprojects@gmail.com")
    location = geolocator.geocode(location)
    return (location.latitude, location.longitude) if location else None

# ✅ Function to Get Directions
def get_directions(start_location, end_location):
    start_coords = get_coordinates(start_location)
    end_coords = get_coordinates(end_location)
    
    if not start_coords or not end_coords:
        return "Error: Invalid location input."
    
    directions = gmaps.directions(start_coords, end_coords, mode="driving")
    steps = directions[0]['legs'][0]['steps']
    
    route_instructions = "Starting Navigation: "
    for step in steps:
        route_instructions += step['html_instructions'].replace('<b>', '').replace('</b>', '') + ". "
    
    return route_instructions

# ✅ Function for Voice-Guided Navigation
def voice_navigation(start, destination):
    route_instructions = get_directions(start, destination)
    print("\n📍 Route Instructions: ", route_instructions)
    
    # Convert text to speech
    tts = gTTS(route_instructions, lang="en")
    tts.save("navigation.mp3")
    
    print("\n🔊 Playing Navigation Instructions...")
    display.display(display.Audio("navigation.mp3", autoplay=True))

# ✅ Example Execution
start_location = "New York, NY"
destination = "Washington, DC"
voice_navigation(start_location, destination)
